# Cursor Rules for saas_cms project

## Git Operations
- NEVER commit or push code to GitHub without explicit user instruction
- Always ask for permission before making any git commits or pushes
- When suggesting changes, ask if the user wants them committed
- Only use git commands when specifically instructed by the user

## Code Changes
- Focus on the current codebase and avoid general answers
- Use design system color tokens instead of hardcoded colors
- Prefer CLI commands over graphical interface instructions
- Don't automatically start development servers

## Deployment
- Don't push to Heroku until explicitly asked

## GitHub Management
- Use GitHub CLI for repository and workflow tasks
- Never push to GitHub without explicit user instructions 

## UI Design 
- Use the ADMIN_PANEL_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md in docs folder to understand the colors and design guidelines 
- Never use hardcoded colors, all from our design system please 
- Make sure to follow the design system religuosly  , if you have any doubt just ask 